==Spanish==
===Etymology===
[[chupar]], ''to [[suck]]'' + [[cabra]], ''[[goat]]''

===Noun===
'''chupacabras''' ''m singular & plural''

# Literally “goat sucker”. A monster said to suck the blood from goats in [[Puerto Rico]], [[Mexico]].  Known in many other South American countries including , [[Peru]], [[Argentina]], [[Uruguay]], and [[Chile]].


